column5: I was in the market for a 6'6"-7' MH baitcasting rod and noticed on Cabelas.ca that they are selling the 7' for $99 down from $220 or so.  Are these any good?  I was leaning towards a Shimano Compre.
From what I hear they are very good.  Recoil eyes?
I have 4 Compres and they're great. I just had a look at the Cabela's XMLTi and it appears to be a pretty sweet rod as well.....If I needed one, I'd be tempted to try one.
